recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community;
Having regard to Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC (1) of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organisation of the market in oils and fats, as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2146/68, (2) and in particular Article 26 (3) thereof;
Whereas Article 6 (2) of Commission Regulation No 282/67/EEC (3) of 11 July 1967 on detailed rules for intervention for oil seeds, as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1486/69, (4) lays down in particular that the intervention agency shall decide on the place where the seeds offered are to be taken over;
Whereas the net losses on purchased products sustained by intervention agencies are eligible under the Guarantee Section of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund ; whereas such losses depend to a great extent on the place and means of storage ; whereas, in order to limit the losses in question, Article 6 of Regulation No 282/67/EEC should be supplemented by defining the criteria for determining the place of taking over;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the Opinion of the Management Committee for Oils and Fats;
